The paper presents extensions to relational topic models for analyzing network data, which involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with document networks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
